In the Admin namespace, the UserController::index method handles GET requests to /admin/users and returns a paginated list of users using paginate(50). Since only pagination is involved and there is no explicit request body or query parameters handled in the method, the only parameter we can deduce from the code is the pagination page query parameter used by Laravelâ€™s paginator. The page parameter is optional and defaults to 1 if not provided. There is no evidence of a per-page or other query parameter being accepted from the request in this method, as the per-page value is hard-coded to 50.
